#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.105"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.105:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.105:0.2"
msgid "11. Sambodhavagga"
msgstr "11. Awakening"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.105:0.3"
msgid "105. Dutiyaassādasutta"
msgstr "105. Gratification (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.260"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: cedaṃ → no cetaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.105:1.1"
msgid ""
"“No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, loke assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā loke sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, if there were no gratification in the world, sentient beings "
"wouldn’t love it."

msgctxt "an3.105:1.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi loke assādo, tasmā sattā loke sārajjanti."
msgstr ""
"But because there is gratification in the world, sentient beings do love it."

msgctxt "an3.105:1.3"
msgid ""
"No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, loke ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā loke nibbindeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the world had no drawback, sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned "
"with it."

msgctxt "an3.105:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi loke ādīnavo, tasmā sattā loke nibbindanti."
msgstr ""
"But because the world has a drawback, sentient beings do grow disillusioned "
"with it."

#. VAR: lokamhā → loke (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.105:1.5"
msgid ""
"No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, loke nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā lokamhā "
"nissareyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If there were no escape from the world, sentient beings wouldn’t escape from "
"it."

msgctxt "an3.105:1.6"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi loke nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā lokamhā "
"nissaranti."
msgstr ""
"But because there is an escape from the world, sentient beings do escape "
"from it."

#. VAR: vippamuttā → vippayuttā (mr)
#. VAR: vimariyādīkatena → vimariyādikatena (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.105:1.7"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, sattā lokassa assādañca assādato ādīnavañca "
"ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsuṃ, neva tāva, "
"bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā "
"pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaṃyuttā vippamuttā vimariyādīkatena cetasā "
"vihariṃsu."
msgstr ""
"As long as sentient beings don’t truly understand the world’s gratification, "
"drawback, and escape for what they are, they haven’t escaped from this world—"
"with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and "
"brahmins, its gods and humans—and they don’t live detached, liberated, with "
"a mind free of limits."

msgctxt "an3.105:1.8"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, sattā lokassa assādañca assādato ādīnavañca "
"ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsuṃ, atha, bhikkhave, "
"sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaṃyuttā vippamuttā vimariyādīkatena cetasā "
"viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But when sentient beings truly understand the world’s gratification, "
"drawback, and escape for what they are, they’ve escaped from this world—with "
"its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and "
"brahmins, its gods and humans—and they live detached, liberated, with a mind "
"free of limits.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.105:1.9"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
